<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 3200, 4100, 4200, 4300, 4400, 7300, 7400, 7500, 7600, 8500, 8600
        Models Built After 05/19/2003 - HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - 4100, 4200, 4300, 4400 - REMOVE AND INSTALL -
        GRILLE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>GRILLE</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Grille - Removal</title>
            <para>The grille is a one piece injection molded assembly, designed with an aerodynamic styling to enhance
                the overall appearance of the 41/42/43/4400 series truck chassis.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0900322" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900322.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 22. Grille And Shroud Removal</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>Refer to Figure 23 for all Items in parentheses.</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the four lower grille and shroud mounting screws on the grille assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900323">Item 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen and remove the screws.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To remove the grille assembly, lift the grille and shroud assembly up and out to release
                    the insert tabs from the grille mounting tab inserts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900323">Item 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Grille - Install</title>
            <para>Prior to installing the grille and shroud assembly, inspect the mounting tabs on the inner upper
                surface of the shroud. Insure that all tabs are functional and in place.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0900323" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900323.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="352px"
                         scalefitheight="352px"/>
                <caption>Figure 23. Grille Installation</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. GRILLE MOUNTING TAB INSERT HOLES</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. LOWER GRILLE MOUNTING POINTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. LOWER GRILLE MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. GRILLE INSERT AND SHROUD</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the mounting tabs with the tab insert holes.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Set the grille/shroud mounting tabs in the insert holes and tilt grille inward and down
                    to locate the lower screw mounting holes.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insure the alignment of the screw mounting holes, insert the four mounting screws in the
                    assembly and tighten.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>Do not overtighten the mounting screws.</para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
